Houston,

Sure. All you need to do is pop up the graphical Python module  
documentation browser that comes with Python. On Windows, it is on the  
Python sub-menu of the Start menu. On other systems, type &#39;pydoc -g&#39;. A  
small window should appear on the screen. Press the button &#39;open  
browser&#39; in this window. A browser window will appear showing a  
document that has links for all installed Python modules. Scroll down  
until you find &#39;Cantera&#39; and follow this link. You will see links for  
all of the modules in the Cantera package.  The gas object belongs to  
class Solution, defined in module &#39;solution&#39;. Follow the &#39;solution&#39;  
link and you will find a complete list of all of the methods you can  
use with gas objects.  Let me know if this doesn&#39;t answer your  
questions.

Dave



